{"entries":[{"id":"tsk-gen-14-2","title":"Genesis 14:2","author":"R. A. Torrey (editor)","reference":{"book":"GEN","chapterStart":14,"verseStart":2,"chapterEnd":14,"verseEnd":2},"content":"<p>Ps 25:10; 103:18; Isa 56:4,5</p>"},{"id":"tsk-gen-14-7","title":"Genesis 14:7","author":"R. A. Torrey (editor)","reference":{"book":"GEN","chapterStart":14,"verseStart":7,"chapterEnd":14,"verseEnd":7},"content":"<p>As. 5; 32:28; 2Sa 12:25 Sarah. i.e., princess.</p>"},{"id":"tsk-gen-14-12","title":"Genesis 14:12","author":"R. A. Torrey (editor)","reference":{"book":"GEN","chapterStart":14,"verseStart":12,"chapterEnd":14,"verseEnd":12},"content":"<p>my. 21:10-12; 26:2-5; 46:1; 48:15; Ex 2:24; 3:6; Lu 1:55,72; Ro 9:5,6,9 Ga 3:29; Heb 11:9 at. 18:10; 21:2,3; Job 14:13; Ac 1:7</p>"},{"id":"tsk-gen-14-17","title":"Genesis 14:17","author":"R. A. Torrey (editor)","reference":{"book":"GEN","chapterStart":14,"verseStart":17,"chapterEnd":14,"verseEnd":17},"content":"<p>circumcised. 18:19</p>"},{"id":"tsk-gen-14-22","title":"Genesis 14:22","author":"R. A. Torrey (editor)","reference":{"book":"GEN","chapterStart":14,"verseStart":22,"chapterEnd":14,"verseEnd":22},"content":"<p>And I. Jud 6:18; 13:15; Mt 6:11 bread.This was the third requisite, and is introduced in its proper order; as eating immediately after exertion or fatigue is very unwholesome.</p>\n<p>comfort. Heb. stay. Jud 19:5; Ps 104:15; Isa 3:1 are ye come. Heb. ye have passed. 19:8; 33:10</p>"}]}